### Edge-function review result (for your note)

I reviewed the edge stack supporting this path: `browse-ai-reviews`, `deep-web-recon`, `social-enrichment`, `market-analysis-ai`, `market-signal-scorer`, `competitor-monitor`, `semrush-domain-intel`.

- **Staff review intelligence source of truth:** `browse-ai-reviews` (+ Serper fallback parsing in backend).
- **SEMrush:** still SEO/paid/competitor intel only (not staff-review source), but now clearly represented in edge-tool metadata.

### Validation

- `python -m py_compile backend/routes/calibration.py` passed.
- Lint diagnostics on all edited files: no issues.
- `deno check` could not be run because `deno` is not installed in this environment.

If you want, I can do a second pass to make the staff card **strictly dated-only** (exclude undated sentiment from pos/neg sections entirely) for an even harder “last 12 months only” interpretation.
